President Obama announced his intent to nominate and appoint several individuals to key administration posts. These include Erin C. Conaton as Under Secretary of Defense for Personnel and Readiness, Scott H. DeLisi as Ambassador to the Republic of Uganda, Deborah Delisle as Assistant Secretary for Elementary and Secondary Education, Tracey Ann Jacobson as Ambassador to the Republic of Kosovo, James J. Jones as Assistant Administrator for Toxic Substances at the Environmental Protection Agency, Frank Kendall III as Under Secretary of Defense for Acquisition, Technology, and Logistics, James N. Miller as Under Secretary of Defense for Policy, Marietta S. Robinson as Commissioner of the Consumer Product Safety Commission, Adam E. Sieminski as Administrator of the Energy Information Administration, John Christopher Stevens as Ambassador to Libya, Linda Thomas-Greenfield as Director General of the Foreign Service, Constance B. Tobias as Chairman of the Board of Veterans' Appeals, Pamela Ann White as Ambassador to the Republic of Haiti, and Jessica Lynn Wright as Assistant Secretary of Defense for Reserve Affairs. President Obama also announced his intent to appoint Eldar Shafir to the President's Advisory Council on Financial Capability, Robert J. Stevens to the Advisory Committee for Trade Policy and Negotiations, and Kimberlydawn Wisdom to the Advisory Group on Prevention, Health Promotion, and Integrative and Public Health.